#HTML HOME:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>        
<head>           
<title>Page Title</title> 
</head>
<body> 

<h1>This is a Heading</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>

</body> 
</html> 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTML INTRODUCTIONS
  PURPOSE OF EACH:
<!DOCTYPE html> Preventing Browser quirk mode, this ensures effort to follow modern HTML specifications rather than outdated uncompatible methods
<html> starting point structure of a html document
<head> meta information about the HTML page
<title> Browser Title Bar Page
<body> defines the document's body, and is a container for all the visible contents, such as headings, paragraphs, images, hyperlinks, tables, lists, etc
<h1> large heading 
<p> paragraph
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTML EDITIORS
  OPEN NOTEPAD (PC)
  WRITE SOME HTML
  SAVE AS "CUSTOM_NAME.HTM" (SET ENCODING TO UTF-8, PREFERRED ENCODING FOR HTML FILES)
  OPEN HTML FILE THAT CAN BE VIEWED IN BROWSER

  OR 

  OPEN TEXTEDIT (MAC)
  (PERFERANCES -> FORMAT -> PLAIN TEXT)
  SAVE AS "CUSTOM_NAME.HTM" (SET ENCODING TO UTF-8, PREFERRED ENCODING FOR HTML FILES)
  OPEN HTML FILE THAT CAN BE VIEWED IN BROWSER
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTML BASICS
  <!DOCTYPE HTML> required
  <HTML>          required

  <a> TAGS FOR LINKS: <a href="https://www.google.com"> This is a link </a>
  <img> TAGS FOR IMAGES <img src="w3schools.jpg" alt="W3Schools.com" width="104" height="142">
  CTRL + U - View Source Code for HTML page.
